Nigerian media mogul and filmmaker, Mo Abudu, and her family are in a celebration mood as they have welcomed a bundle of joy as an addition to their family. The founder of Ebonylife TV took to her verified Instagram account to share the good news, saying, “Good morning beautiful people. All glory to God, 2 weeks ago I became a grandmother for the 2nd time. TJ now has a baby brother, Ireoluwa. BBC employs DJ Cuppy as Radio Presenter Kano censorship board, film producer at loggerheads over new film teaser “It’s an amazing feeling, being a grandmother to two amazing boys. Seeing my dear mum now 80 and grandpa Abudu, 95 now great grandparents for the second time gives our families priceless joy. “My darling Temidee and Adebola, congratulations. I pray God keeps you all enveloped in his arms now and always. To the entire family, grandmas, grandpas, aunties and uncles, we praise God for the blessing to our family.” (sic) Last February, the Ebony TV boss, while announcing the birth of her first grandchild, said via the verified Instagram page, “All glory to God, I became a grandma today. My darling Temidee gave birth to a bouncing baby boy. Lord, I am so so grateful. Dear Temidayo and Adebola, my biggest congratulations. God’s love, favour and blessings now and always.” (sic)